-- Gold Shares Fall, Strike Hits AngloGold: Johannesburg Mover
-- B y   J a c o   V i s s e r
-- 2012-10-19T08:51:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-19/gold-shares-fall-strike-hits-anglogold-johannesburg-mover.html
The  FTSE/JSE Africa Gold Mining
Index (JGOLD)  fell to its lowest level in more than a month as strikes
continue at South African gold mines.  The index declined 1.7 percent to 2,309 points by 9:30 a.m.
extending its decline to a third day. Shares in  AngloGold
Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) , the world’s third-largest producer of the metal,
fell 2.3 percent to reach its lowest level in more than a month.
The stock traded at 281.25 rand ($32.51) by 9:30 a.m. in
Johannesburg.  All AngloGold’s employees are still on strike, spokesman
Alan Fine said by phone today.  Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HAR) , Africa’s
third-largest producer of the metal, said 5,400 miners at its
Kusasalethu operation are absent.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI) , the world’s fourth-largest producer of
the metal, today said an unauthorized strike at its KDC West
mine is over.  To contact the reporter on this story:
